{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% set honest = card_data.managers.honest %}
{% set overlaid = card_data.managers.overlaid %}
{% set comp = overlaid.screen.composite %}
{% set gate = overlaid.screen.power_gate %}

{% macro diag_label(name) %}{{ {
  "treynor_mazuy": "Treynor–Mazuy γ (curvature)",
  "updown_beta": "Up/down β gap (β⁺ − β⁻)",
  "market_coskew": "Market coskewness",
  "drawdown_vol": "Drawdown vs vol signature",
  "straddle_loading": "Fung–Hsieh straddle loading"
}[name] }}{% endmacro %}

{% macro verdict_token(v) %}{{ "shrink" if v == "short-vol-consistent" else ("noise" if v in ["inconclusive", "not-played"] else "robust") }}{% endmacro %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/m2.css">
{% endblock %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="m2-intro">
  <p class="m2-headline">
    Two synthetic managers, one market, {{ card_data.meta.months }} months.
    <strong>{{ honest.name }}</strong> and
    <strong>{{ overlaid.name }}</strong> report the <em>same</em> Sharpe to two
    decimals ({{ "%.2f"|format(honest.sharpe.point) }}) &mdash; but one is quietly
    short volatility. Their payoff shapes reveal the difference before the
    supporting diagnostics do.
  </p>
  <aside class="m2-disclosure" role="note">
    The overlaid book's written-put premium is calibrated in-sample and set
    <strong>rich of fair</strong> &mdash; above the actuarial cost of its
    payouts &mdash; so both books report the same healthy Sharpe: the classic
    carry seduction, where selling insurance above cost flatters every
    average-based statistic. That calibration is a deliberate look-ahead for a
    controlled demonstration and <strong>not a claim about live methodology</strong>
    &mdash; a real short-vol book's premium is set ex-ante. Separate calibration
    tests use <strong>fair premium</strong> (zero in-sample carry), the conservative
    case. Fully synthetic; manager names are fictional.
  </aside>
</section>

<section class="m2-payoff" aria-labelledby="m2-payoff-title">
  <div class="m2-payoff__heading">
    <div>
      <p class="m2-payoff__eyebrow">Paired payoff shapes</p>
      <h2 id="m2-payoff-title">The same reported Sharpe can hide opposite tail behavior</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Each dot is one aligned month. Both charts use the same horizontal and vertical scales.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="m2-payoff__grid">
    {% for key, m, label in [
      ("honest", honest, "Honest return process"),
      ("overlaid", overlaid, "Written-put overlay")
    ] %}
    <figure class="m2-payoff-figure">
      <figcaption><strong>{{ label }}</strong><span>{{ m.name }}</span></figcaption>
      <div class="m2-payoff-frame">
        <span class="m2-payoff-axis m2-payoff-axis--y">Manager return (%)</span>
        <svg class="m2-payoff-chart" data-series="{{ key }}"
             data-common-domain="paired-payoff" viewBox="0 0 320 220" role="img"
             aria-label="{{ m.name }} monthly manager returns against the same monthly market returns"></svg>
        <span class="m2-payoff-axis m2-payoff-axis--x">Market return (%)</span>
      </div>
    </figure>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <p class="m2-payoff__takeaway"><strong>What changes:</strong> the overlaid manager bends down in
    the market&rsquo;s worst months. <strong>What does not:</strong> the reported Sharpe rounds to
    {{ "%.2f"|format(honest.sharpe.point) }} for both managers.</p>
</section>

<section class="m2-exhibit" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <h2 class="m2-section__title">What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <div class="m2-exhibit__block">
    <h3 class="m2-exhibit__subtitle">What you are looking at</h3>
    <p class="m2-note">
      {{ honest.name }} and {{ overlaid.name }} both report a Sharpe of
      {{ "%.2f"|format(honest.sharpe.point) }} over the same
      {{ card_data.meta.months }} months and the same market &mdash; a linear tear
      sheet cannot tell them apart. The convexity screen reads payoff <em>shape</em>
      instead of the average: it leaves {{ honest.name }} unflagged
      ({{ honest.screen.composite.short_vol_count }} of
      {{ honest.screen.composite.playable_count }} diagnostics fire) and flags
      {{ overlaid.name }} for investigation
      ({{ overlaid.screen.composite.short_vol_count }} of
      {{ overlaid.screen.composite.playable_count }} fire, at the threshold of
      {{ overlaid.screen.composite.k }}). The stress-month table below shows the
        months the hidden written put paid out &mdash; the two books are similar
      until the tail arrives.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="m2-exhibit__block">
    <h3 class="m2-exhibit__subtitle">How to read it</h3>
    <ul class="m2-exhibit__map">
      <li><strong>Payoff shapes</strong> &mdash; the two charts share both axes. The overlaid
        manager bends downward in the worst market months while the honest process does not.</li>
      <li><strong>Reported-Sharpe interval bands</strong> &mdash; each manager's
        Sharpe point marker sits inside its 95% interval; the two bands overlap, which
        is the whole point: the average-based statistic separates nothing.</li>
      <li><strong>Composite verdict chip</strong> &mdash; the badge under each manager.
        {{ overlaid.name }} reads <code>SHORT-VOL POSTURE &mdash; INVESTIGATE</code>
        (a <em>shrink</em> chip); {{ honest.name }} reads a <em>noise</em> chip,
        &ldquo;not resolvable at this track length.&rdquo; It is an investigation
        prompt, never an accusation.</li>
      <li><strong>Diagnostic interval-stats</strong> &mdash; the four playable windows
        onto {{ overlaid.name }}'s payoff shape, each a 90% interval. An interval
        sitting fully beyond its calibrated short-vol boundary counts toward the tally.
        Market coskewness can clear zero and still read <em>inconclusive</em>: its entire
        interval must clear &minus;{{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.meta.coskew_band) }}, not merely zero.</li>
      <li><strong>Missing diagnostic</strong> &mdash; the Fung&ndash;Hsieh straddle test is
        not calculated because its public PTFS factor series has not been connected.</li>
      <li><strong>Tail-loss months</strong> &mdash; the table of months the put
        paid out, with the market move and both books' returns side by side.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="m2-note">
      The full methodology &mdash; with the math and a reference implementation
      &mdash; is in the
      <a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/{{ card.id }}.html">technical method</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="m2-pair">
  {% for key, m in [("honest", honest), ("overlaid", overlaid)] %}
  <article class="m2-manager m2-manager--{{ key }}">
    <h2 class="m2-manager__name">{{ m.name }}</h2>
    <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="sharpe"
         data-lo="{{ m.sharpe.ci_lo }}" data-point="{{ m.sharpe.point }}" data-hi="{{ m.sharpe.ci_hi }}">
      <span class="interval-stat__label">Reported Sharpe</span>
      <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%.2f"|format(m.sharpe.point) }}</span>
      <div class="interval-stat__rail"><div class="interval-stat__band"></div><div class="interval-stat__point"></div></div>
      <span class="interval-stat__range">95% interval {{ "%.2f"|format(m.sharpe.ci_lo) }} &hellip; {{ "%.2f"|format(m.sharpe.ci_hi) }}</span>
    </div>
    <span class="verdict-chip m2-composite" data-verdict="{{ m.screen.composite.chip }}">{{ m.screen.composite.label }}</span>
    <p class="m2-tally">{{ m.screen.composite.short_vol_count }} of {{ m.screen.composite.playable_count }} playable diagnostics short-vol-consistent (flag at {{ m.screen.composite.k }}).</p>
  </article>
  {% endfor %}
</section>

<section class="m2-diagnostics">
  <h2 class="m2-section__title">Four windows onto one shape &mdash; {{ overlaid.name }}</h2>
  <p class="m2-note">Converging evidence, not a p-value. Each diagnostic reads the same left-tail geometry; the tally is agreement across windows, never a manufactured joint significance.</p>
  {% for name, d in overlaid.screen.diagnostics.items() %}
  {% if d.played %}
  <div class="interval-stat" data-domain="{{ name }}"
       data-lo="{{ d.ci_lo }}" data-point="{{ d.point }}" data-hi="{{ d.ci_hi }}"
       {% if name == "market_coskew" %}data-decision-low="{{ -card_data.meta.coskew_band }}"
       data-decision-high="{{ card_data.meta.coskew_band }}"{% endif %}
       data-verdict="{{ verdict_token(d.verdict) }}">
    <span class="interval-stat__label">{{ diag_label(name) }}</span>
    <span class="interval-stat__value">{{ "%+.3f"|format(d.point) }}</span>
    <div class="interval-stat__rail">
      {% if name == "market_coskew" %}
      <div class="m2-decision-band" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="m2-decision-boundary m2-decision-boundary--low" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="m2-decision-boundary m2-decision-boundary--high" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      {% endif %}
      <div class="interval-stat__band"></div><div class="interval-stat__point"></div>
    </div>
    <span class="interval-stat__range">90% interval {{ "%+.3f"|format(d.ci_lo) }} &hellip; {{ "%+.3f"|format(d.ci_hi) }} &mdash; {{ d.verdict }}</span>
  </div>
  {% else %}
  <div class="power-gate m2-rung-unplayed">
    <span class="power-gate__title">{{ diag_label(name) }}</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason"><strong>Not calculated:</strong> the public Fung&ndash;Hsieh PTFS
      factor series has not been connected. No substitute value is fabricated.</p>
  </div>
  {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
  <p class="m2-coskew-note">The coskew rail shades the calibrated decision band
    &minus;{{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.meta.coskew_band) }} to
    +{{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.meta.coskew_band) }}. Its 90% interval clears zero but its
    upper endpoint does not clear the &minus;{{ "%.2f"|format(card_data.meta.coskew_band) }}
    boundary, so the diagnostic remains inconclusive and the composite remains 3 of 4.</p>
  <p class="m2-downleg-note">The up/down β gap is a <strong>static payoff-shape descriptor</strong>, never a conditional-alpha table. Its down-leg is identified off ~19 down-months at T = 48, so its interval is honestly wide.</p>
</section>

{% if not gate.open %}
<section class="m2-powergate">
  <div class="power-gate">
    <span class="power-gate__title">power gate</span>
    <p class="power-gate__reason">{{ gate.reason }}</p>
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

<section class="m2-stress">
  <h2 class="m2-section__title">Tail-loss months</h2>
  <p class="m2-note">The months the written put paid out show where the apparently similar books diverged.</p>
  <svg class="m2-stress-strip" viewBox="0 0 100 30" preserveAspectRatio="none" role="img" aria-label="Honest vs overlaid monthly returns"></svg>
  <table class="m2-stress-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Month</th><th>Market</th><th>{{ honest.name }}</th><th>{{ overlaid.name }}</th><th>Put payout</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for s in card_data.stress_months %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ s.month }}</td>
        <td>{{ "%+.1f"|format(s.market_factor * 100) }}%</td>
        <td>{{ "%+.1f"|format(s.honest_return * 100) }}%</td>
        <td class="m2-stress-hit">{{ "%+.1f"|format(s.overlaid_return * 100) }}%</td>
        <td>&minus;{{ "%.1f"|format(s.payout * 100) }}%</td>
      </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>Five returns-based convexity diagnostics over a de-smoothed return series: a
Treynor&ndash;Mazuy quadratic term, a Henriksson&ndash;Merton up/down β gap,
Harvey&ndash;Siddique market coskewness, a drawdown-vs-vol signature (reusing the
companion drawdown band read for asymmetry), and &mdash; where the external Fung&ndash;Hsieh
straddle series is loaded &mdash; a PTFS loading. Each is a single static shape
coefficient over the whole window, interval-reported by a circular block
bootstrap; none is a regime split or a time-varying beta.</p>
<p>The composite is an <em>evidence tally</em>, not a score and not a p-value: it
flags <em>investigate</em> only when at least {{ comp.k }} playable diagnostics
agree in the short-vol direction and the power gate for this track length is
open. De-smoothing first is the load-bearing false-alarm control &mdash; it keeps
an honest-but-smooth illiquid book from being mistaken for a short-vol one. The
T &ge; 48 render gate is provisional &mdash; the calibrated false-alarm and detection
curves that pin it land with the atlas build.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/m2-convexity.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
